    {"@type":"Question","name":"Why does my Perth business need a business-grade firewall?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A business-grade firewall (Fortinet FortiGate, Cisco Meraki) provides intrusion prevention, DNS filtering, application control and detailed traffic logging that consumer-grade routers lack entirely — critical for protecting Perth SMBs from ransomware and data breaches."}},
    {"@type":"Question","name":"Can EvoTech design and install a network for a new Perth office?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. EvoTech Digital provides end-to-end network design and installation for new Perth offices — cabling, rack build, firewall configuration, Wi-Fi deployment, VLAN segmentation and ongoing managed network support."}},
    {"@type":"Question","name":"How much does business networking cost for a small Perth office?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A basic business network for a small Perth office (firewall/router, managed switch, 2-3 Wi-Fi APs) typically starts from $1,200-$2,500 in hardware plus installation labour. Contact EvoTech Digital for a free site assessment and transparent quote."}},
